name: Habitat for Humanity International
mission: Habitat for Humanity is a movement of people in your local area and around the world, working together to build more prosperous and vibrant communities by making sure everyone has a safe, affordable place to call home. Since our founding in 1976 as a Christian organization, together we have helped more than 62 million people globally build their futures on their own terms through access to decent housing. We’ve done that by working alongside people of all walks of life to build, repair and finance their homes, by innovating new ways of building and financing, and by advocating for policies that make constructing and accessing housing easier for everyone. Together, we build homes, communities and hope. To learn more, visit habitat.org
programs: Terwilliger Center for Innovation in Shelter
theoryOfChange: The site states that every safe, affordable home sparks wider change, leading to better health, education and well-being, more economic growth and less poverty, and that it starts with a home.

strengths.detail: The organization holds an <cite id="8">overall score of 98.98.5/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>, reflecting near-perfect marks for accountability and transparency.
Habitat directs <cite id="9">77.5% of its total expenses toward program services</cite>, exceeding the peer median for domestic poverty organizations.

strengths_deep_dive: Habitat for Humanity's financial health is anchored by its strong liquidity and diversified revenue streams. With <cite id="11">$305,651,094 in public contributions</cite> and over $12 million in program service revenue, the organization is not dependent on a single funding source. Its governance is equally strong, featuring an <cite id="12">independent board of 23 members</cite> and a Gold Seal of Transparency from Candid. This institutional maturity allows them to manage complex grantmaking, distributing <cite id="13">$121,259,158 in total grants</cite> to local affiliates and international partners to ensure localized impact.
rich_narrative.summary: Habitat for Humanity International Inc is a global housing organization that has operated since <cite id="1">its founding in 1976</cite> to address systemic housing inequities through direct shelter provision and community development. The organization maintains a massive operational scale, reporting <cite id="2">$329,195,153 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 fiscal year. Its primary mission involves moving families from ruin to recovery by building and improving homes in <cite id="3">over 70 countries</cite>, including regions across Africa, Mexico, and South America. Beyond physical construction, Habitat engages in systemic change through initiatives like the <cite id="4">Cost of Home advocacy campaign</cite> and the Home Equals global advocacy program. The organization is highly efficient in its resource mobilization, maintaining <cite id="5">fundraising efficiency of $0.21 per $1 raised</cite>, which is well within the top tier for domestic poverty organizations. Financially, the charity is robust, holding <cite id="6">$565,862,638 in total assets</cite> and demonstrating significant liquidity with <cite id="7">15.6 months of working capital</cite> to sustain its global operations.
